This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial recognition and verification using biometric technology. The use of convolution neural networks and multiple kernel learning methods also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the vulnerability of face biometrics to spoofing attacks, which falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of image processing techniques such as anisotropic diffusion suggests that it may also belong to the Image and Video Processing (cs.IR) sub-category.
